main event: Several unidentified flying objects were observed and filmed over Yonkers, New York on March 19, 1967.
interesting points: The sighting lasted approximately 45 minutes,The witness reported filming the objects but described the images as blurred,The objects were observed from a 16th-floor apartment,The witness expressed interest in receiving feedback and analysis of the film submitted to the Air Force,Colonel Manaff's correspondence indicated long processing times for film evaluations.
witness description: A civilian observer and a companion watching from an apartment
